    "body": "Hey @borismelnik @John-44 \r\n\r\nI've added an example of a pinned message which includes a gallery of images in situ of both the main chat area and the pinned messages dialog.\r\n\r\nInside the pinned messages dialog, we remove any independent image and link interactions - so clicking anywhere on the gallery message inside that dialog (including on an image) should cause the dialog to close and the user to be auto-scrolled to the relevant message in situ. (This is how it works now anyway - we can always revisit if we agree we want to allow light-boxing of images and links to be clickable globally for pinned messages)\r\n\r\nBoth designs (the gallery message inside the chat and that inside the dialog) are essentially the same.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"Pinned message - edit\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/9fd1cf93-c1d8-4f62-8638-bbd4661d1ffc\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"Pinned message with image gallery\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/4b8b3ab4-f5d2-449c-aa34-d11e1016a3a4\">\r\n\r\nFigma links (`Chat | Desktop` Figma file):\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/Mr3rqxxgKJ2zMQ06UAKiWL/%F0%9F%92%AC-Chat%E2%8E%9CDesktop?type=design&node-id=21982-657117&t=D998NtlASOPeLoyb-4\r\n\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/Mr3rqxxgKJ2zMQ06UAKiWL/%F0%9F%92%AC-Chat%E2%8E%9CDesktop?type=design&node-id=21982-655449&t=D998NtlASOPeLoyb-4\r\n\r\nCaybro has done a lot of work on pinned messages recently following the below issue so might be worth giving him a ping to see if there is anything that can be leveraged as a basis :)\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/9396#issuecomment-1412364116\r\n\r\n",
